# 🤝 Contributing Guide

Welcome!

Thank you for contributing to the Cohort 20 Telegram Bot.

This project exists to help everyone learn software engineering through collaboration.

---

# Before You Start

1. Join the GitHub repository.
2. Read the README.
3. Pick an Issue.
4. Ask questions if you're stuck.

---

# Workflow

We use Git Flow.

```
main
│
develop
│
feature/your-feature
```

Never work directly on **main**.

---

# Creating a Branch

Example

```bash
git checkout develop

git pull

git checkout -b feature/welcome-message
```

---

# Making Changes

Commit often.

Good commit messages

```
Add welcome message

Fix reminder bug

Implement FAQ command
```

Avoid messages like

```
update

fixed

done

asdf
```

---

# Push Your Branch

```bash
git push origin feature/welcome-message
```

---

# Open a Pull Request

Describe

- What you changed
- Why you changed it
- Screenshots (if applicable)

Wait for review before merging.

---

# Coding Standards

- Write clean code.
- Keep functions small.
- Comment difficult logic.
- Remove unused code.
- Test before pushing.

---

# Documentation

If you build something:

Record a short video.

Explain

- What you built
- Why
- Challenges faced

Business Analysis students will use these videos to create the project journal.

---

# Need Help?

Ask in

- Telegram
- WhatsApp

Don't stay stuck.

---

Happy Coding 🚀
